column5: I know you're likely working on a full report, but give us a little hint on how Dusey went? I was watching the weather up there last week and it looked like you had great conditions. If you did go for some pike and walleye I bet they were on fire.
Mike called me when he got back, should be a interesting report

It was amazing Chris, maybe the best fly in I've ever done.  The brook trout fishing was incredible, honestly it was hard to tear myself away from it. The Dusey river was just phenominal.  Walleye and pike fishing in the lake and parts of the river was just as good.  Fantastic cabin as well with a Bosch on demand hot water heater.  I'll have something posted by next week.
wow, possibly the best fly-in you've done? should be a cool report, I've said it before, I'm going to say it again, you're a lucky guy, I'm jealous again
Nah, I'd say he has earned 'em.
Excellent, that's what I'm aiming for. LOL!   Maybe you can join me on one of these trips sometime.
